<item>
            <title>[SPARK-36552] varchar datatype behave differently on  hive table  and datasource table</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-36552</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in spark 3.1.X, when set spark.sql.hive.convertMetastoreOrc=false,and&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;spark.sql.legacy.charVarcharAsString=true.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Execute the following sql:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;CREATE TABLE t (col varchar(2)) stored as orc;&lt;br/&gt;
INSERT INTO t SELECT &apos;aaa&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
select * from t;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;result is aa&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But when set&#160;spark.sql.hive.convertMetastoreOrc=true,and&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;spark.sql.legacy.charVarcharAsString=true&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;alse execute the sql, the result is &quot;aaa&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
